  "texts": [
    "On AZ-DR-R2, we notice a large uplift just by the simple inclusion of low-fidelity labels (from 0.049 to 0.331 in R 2 for the 1K split).",
    "In contrast, the best performance of non-augmented models is achieved for the 5K training set size (R 2 of 0.220), which is more than 50% lower than the performance on the 1K set with low-fidelity labels.",
    "Adaptive embeddings produced in a transductive setting improve over 8 times over the baseline R 2 (0.455) and by 37.39% over the raw labels.",
    "The adaptive embeddings produced in an inductive setting generally match the raw labels, even outperforming them for the 1K training set size.",
    "Both sum embeddings perform similarly, improving upon the baseline but not matching the raw labels."
  ],
